owerups are quite common, but you need to match and remove 500 potions to get one. You can pay Gold to buy powerups if you run out of them.(P2W, huh?)\n- The bonus bombs on removing 4 or 5 tiles can only be created in first move, unlike other Match-3s where you can get them from combos. Swap two bombs for bigger explosion, but it's much harder to actually do so and there won't be much space to make multiple bombs.\n- You can get bonus resources if you swap & match in certian order(shown on the top of screen), though it's nothing but a waste of moves. \n- Getting 3-star gets difficult due to very low moves, and Medals require 100%'ing the boards(Open all chests, remove dirt/sand tiles, deplete all resource stockpiles, destroy all crates). This means YOU MUST PAY GOLD TO GET MEDALS, because Gold Chests are also counted for the Medal.\n- As for Stars and Medals, you will NEED them to progress.\n- The cave levels have TOO MUCH moves available. And in earlier level without light radius upgrades, it irritated me often when I don't \"see\" any matchable blocks, but the game knows there are matchable blocks IN THE DARKNESS.\n\nThe game has potential and could've been great if it focused on \"pay for the package, and everything else is free, no currencies bullshit\".\nI can't really understand why they made decisions to make the game less engaging, by adding lots of \"Gold contents\" that basically slows game down, and ignoring the standards of Match-3 games(such as bombs creation in combos and shuffles).", "votes_down": 1, "language": "english", "comment_count": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "timestamp_updated": 1503279503, "timestamp_created": 1502597757, "written_during_early_access": false, "author": {"playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "steamid": "76561197960332616", "num_reviews": 37, "num_games_owned": 4480, "last_played": 1504235091, "playtime_forever": 1365}, "votes_up": 17, "voted_up": false}], "success": 1}